feat: Implement ATM finder using OpenStreetMap data
This commit introduces functionality to find and display nearby ATMs using data fetched from the OpenStreetMap Overpass API.
Backend: - Adds a new endpoint `/api/atms/nearby/` that accepts latitude, longitude, and radius to search for ATMs. - Parses ATM data (name, operator, opening hours, coordinates, OSM ID) from the Overpass API. - Includes `requests` in backend dependencies.
Frontend: - Modifies `MapPage.tsx` to fetch ATM data from the new backend endpoint. - Implements your geolocation (with fallback to a default location) to find nearby ATMs. - Replaces hardcoded bank data with dynamically fetched ATM data. - Updates `Map.tsx` and the list view in `MapPage.tsx` to display ATM information, including name, operator (if available), and opening hours (if available). - Handles loading and error states gracefully. - Implements two-way selection synchronization between the map markers and the list items for a cohesive user experience. - Removes or repurposes UI elements not applicable to ATM data (e.g., ratings, detailed services not provided by OSM).
Documentation: - Adds details of the new backend ATM endpoint to `docs/backend/README.md`. - Updates frontend documentation for `MapPage.tsx` to reflect its new capabilities in `docs/frontend/src/pages/MapPage.md`.
